# Install terraform in Linux machine

      Create the directory with the following command: mkdir terraform && cd terraform
      
      Then, download Terraform using this command: wget https://releases.hashicorp.com/terraform/0.11.14/terraform_0.11.14_linux_amd64.zip
      
      Install a program called ‘unzip’ in order to unpack the download by entering the following: Sudo yum install unzip
      
      Once installed, unpack the Terraform download: unzip terraform_0.11.14_linux_amd64.zip
      
      Set the Linux path to point to Terraform with the following command: export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/terraform
      
      Test that Terraform is installed by typing this command: terraform
